{
  "info": {
    "name": "security-starter-app",
    "description": "Complete API surface of the consumer app on http://localhost:8081 — every endpoint exposed by the 10 consumer controllers and the 7 starter (com.vn.security.core) controllers that the app re-exposes.\n\nFolder layout:\n- 🔐 Auth          — login / register / refresh / logout / change-password\n- 📋 Catalog       — Tags, Domains, Organizations CRUD\n- 📦 Meta          — Packs, Sets, SetVersions, Sources, Syncs, Public preview\n- 🛡 Admin (starter)— Roles, Permissions, MenuDefinitions, MenuPermissions, Catalog\n- 🔍 Security info — Authorities, current-user menu permissions, entity capabilities\n- ✅ RBAC tests    — 7 status-code-asserting requests (anon / admin / user x read / write)\n- 🔄 Token lifecycle— refresh rotation + reuse-must-fail + change-password + logout\n- 💾 Cache probe   — admin role update -> watch Hazelcast maps clear\n\nCollection-level pre-request script auto-runs admin login when {{adminToken}} is empty, so any single request can be invoked without manually running the Auth folder first. The RBAC tests still benefit from running top-to-bottom because they depend on {{userToken}} as well.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-login the admin if no token yet. Runs at most once per Postman session.",
          "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('adminToken');",
          "if (token && token.length > 0) return;",
          "const baseUrl = pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl') || pm.variables.get('baseUrl');",
          "pm.sendRequest({",
          "  url: baseUrl + '/api/auth/login',",
          "  method: 'POST',",
          "  header: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},",
          "  body: {mode: 'raw', raw: JSON.stringify({username: 'admin', password: 'admin'})}",
          "}, (err, res) => {",
          "  if (err || res.code !== 200) return;",
          "  const body = res.json();",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('adminToken', body.accessToken);",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('adminRefreshToken', body.refreshToken);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🔐 Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login admin",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
            "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const body = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('adminToken', body.accessToken);",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('adminRefreshToken', body.refreshToken);"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"password\": \"admin\"\n}"},
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Register testuser (idempotent)",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
            "pm.test('201 created or 409 already exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"testuser\",\n  \"password\": \"pass1234\",\n  \"email\": \"testuser@localhost\",\n  \"firstName\": \"Test\",\n  \"lastName\": \"User\"\n}"},
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login testuser",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
            "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const body = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('userToken', body.accessToken);",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('userRefreshToken', body.refreshToken);"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"testuser\",\n  \"password\": \"pass1234\"\n}"},
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh access token",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
            "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const body = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.test('returns NEW refreshToken (single-use rotation)', () => {",
            "  pm.expect(body.refreshToken).to.not.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('userRefreshToken'));",
            "});",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('userToken', body.accessToken);",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('userRefreshToken', body.refreshToken);"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{userRefreshToken}}\"\n}"},
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Change password (user)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{userToken}}"}, {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"currentPassword\": \"pass1234\",\n  \"newPassword\": \"pass5678\"\n}"},
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout (admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}"}],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
